    quote: "If people are not laughing at your goals, your goals are too small.",
    story: "Key: Azim Premji’s journey is a masterclass in vision, discipline, and unprecedented generosity. At just 21, he was forced to drop out of Stanford University to take over his father’s Western Indian Vegetable Products company following his sudden demise. What began as a small cooking oil business in Amalner was **transformed** by Premji into Wipro, a global information technology giant. Under his leadership, Wipro pivoted from vegetable oils to hydraulic cylinders and eventually to software services, becoming one of the first Indian companies to compete on the world stage.\n\nKnown as the 'Czar of the Indian IT Industry,' Premji is equally famous for his incredible frugality and его belief in simple living. Despite his immense wealth, he famously flew economy and stayed in company guesthouses. However, his true legacy lies in his philanthropy. He was the first Indian to sign The Giving Pledge and has donated over $21 billion to his foundation — nearly 67% of Wipro's shares. The Azim Premji Foundation works tirelessly across thousands of schools in rural India, reflecting his conviction that quality primary education is the only way to build a more equitable and human society. His life proves that true success is measured not by what you accumulate, but by what you give back to the world.",
