    quote: "If you want to walk fast, walk alone. But if you want to walk far, walk together.",
    story: "Gautam Adani's rise from a college dropout to one of the world's wealthiest men is a testament to grit and ambition. Starting as a diamond sorter in Mumbai, he **founded** Adani Enterprises in 1988 as a commodity trading firm.\n\nKey: He identified the potential of infrastructure early on, developing Mundra Port into India's largest private port. Today, the Adani Group spans ports, airports, power, green energy, and cement.\n\nDespite controversies, his focus on building critical infrastructure has made him a central figure in India's economic growth story.",
