    quote: "What started as a small farm became a life-changing journey of growth and purpose.",
    story: "Janardan Khorate, popularly known as ‘Saladbaba’ in Goa, **transformed** a small organic farming initiative into a multi-crore enterprise. His journey took a pivotal turn in 2003 when David Grower and Michaela Kelemen, a couple from London who had started Ambrosia Organic Farm in Goa, adopted him and took him to London for education and a better future.\n\nOriginally started in 1993 as a 5-acre farm in Siolim, Ambrosia supplied fresh vegetables like tomatoes and capsicum to local restaurants, earning its nickname ‘Saladbaba’. Over time, the venture expanded into products like peanut butter, rice, and chia seeds.\n\nKey: In 2008, Janardan was entrusted with managing the farm. With dedication and vision, he scaled the business from a modest Rs 20 lakh turnover to an impressive Rs 22 crore annually.\n\nToday, Ambrosia spans 135 acres and serves numerous restaurants and cafes across Goa, standing as a pioneer in India’s organic farming movement. Janardan’s journey reflects how opportunity, trust, and hard work can transform not just a business, but an entire life.",
