    knownFor: "Global domination in entertainment",
    quote: "You have to teach yourself to take over the world.",
    story: "Priyanka Chopra Jonas’s journey is a masterclass in the power of relentless ambition and the ability to reinvent oneself on a global stage. Winning the Miss World title at the age of 18 was just the beginning. She quickly rose to become one of Bollywood's highest-paid and most versatile actors, known for taking on unconventional roles that challenged the traditional 'heroine' mold.\n\nKey: Not content with being a superstar in India, she took a massive risk by moving to the United States to start from scratch. She became the first South Asian woman to headline an American network drama series, 'Quantico', and has since built a successful career in Hollywood as an actor and producer. Beyond the screen, Priyanka is a UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador and a savvy tech investor, using her platform to advocate for children’s rights and girls' education. Her memoir, 'Unfinished', captures her journey of breaking through the 'glass ceiling' multiple times. She remains a symbol of the 'Global Indian'—someone who is deeply rooted in her heritage but fearless in her pursuit of the world. Her life is a reminder that no dream is too big if you are willing to work harder than anyone else in the room.",
