    quote: "True teachers are those who help us think for ourselves.",
    story: "Dr. Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan was a towering intellectual who served as a bridge between the philosophical traditions of the East and the West. A brilliant scholar and orator, he spent his early career as a professor of philosophy at prestigious institutions like Oxford University and the University of Calcutta. He was known for his ability to translate complex Vedantic concepts into a language that the modern world could understand, earning him global respect as an original thinker.\n\nKey: When he became the second **President of India** in 1962, some of his students and friends requested him to allow them to celebrate his birthday. In his characteristic humility, he replied, 'Instead of celebrating my birthday, it would be my proud privilege if September 5th is observed as Teachers' Day.' This gesture was a reflection of his belief that the teacher is the most important part of a nation’s foundation. He famously said that 'teachers should be the best minds in the country.' His legacy lives on every year on Teachers' Day, serving as a reminder of the dignity of the teaching profession and the power of knowledge to transform individuals and societies. He remains a symbol of the philosopher-king, a leader whose authority came from his wisdom and character.",
